                  <decoDesc>
                    <summary>Miniatures, all in the late twentieth-century hand of the “speckled garment artist,” painted over text</summary>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#ir" facs="001">Fol. ir</locus>
                        <desc>Image of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6387Luke">Luke</persName>
                           <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1014Evangelists">Evangelists</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#4r" facs="006">Fol. 4r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#28r" facs="030">Fol. 28r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> brandishing a <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/></desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#56v" facs="059">Fol. 56v</locus>
                        <desc>
                           <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/>, <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#81r" facs="083">Fol. 81r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1067LastSupper">The Last Supper</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">
                        <locus target="#101r" facs="103">Fol. 101r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1024MosesLaw">Moses Receiving Law</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7">
                        <locus target="#119v" facs="122">Fol. 119v</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1008Descent">Descent into Hell</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8">
                        <locus target="#120r" facs="122">Fol. 120r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1033Ascension">Ascension of Jesus</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d9">Decorative designs: <locus target="#37r">fol. 37r</locus> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using black)</decoNote>

                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="Asmat">
                              <locus target="#iv #iir" facs="002">Fols. iv, iir</locus> Asmat prayer to protect domestic animals from wild animals</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc type="ReceiptNote">
                              <locus target="#iir" facs="002">Fol. iir</locus> Receipt of the purchase of the manuscript</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#1r" facs="003">Fol. 1r</locus> The title of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1099Anapho">ʾAkkʷateta qʷǝrbān
                                                  za-qǝddus Hǝryāqos za-hagara Bǝhnǝsā</ref>, the Anaphora of Our Lady by Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <desc type="ScribalNoteCommissioning">Copied for <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብራ፡ መድኅን፡ አበበ፡</foreign>, <locus target="#81r" facs="083">fol. 81r</locus>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <desc>Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#4r #5v #6r #29v #30r #31v #32r #33r #33v #37v #47r #61v #63r #68v #75v" facs="006 008 008 032 032 034 034 035 036 040 049 064 065 071 078">folss. 4r, 5v, 6r, 29v, 30r, 31v, 32r, 33r, 33v, 37v, 47r, 61v, 63r, 68v, 75v, </locus>);
                        and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#71v" facs="074">71v</locus>)</desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#1r" facs="003">Fol. 1r</locus> blank</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, three Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards. Inside the back cover, a portion of the wood has been scraped lower than the rest, forming an area 70 x 60 mm. It looks to have held a mirror at some time though now all that appears to remain is the residue of old glue.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                    </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
